def: Something actually received; real, as distinct from estimated,receipts. [Cant]The accounts of revenues supplied . . . were not real receipts: not,in financial language, "actuals," but only Egyptian budget estimates.Fortnightly Review.
A picture made up of several smaller pictures, drawn uponseparate pieces in such a manner as to admit of combination in manydifferent ways, thus producing a great variety of scenes orlandscapes.
A small gable, or gable-shaped canopy, formed over atabernacle, niche, etc.
A division of a tribe; a group of genera of a little lower rankthan a tribe.
Things so unequal or unlike that they can not be compared witheach other.
Holing a ball, whether the object ball (winning hazard) or theplayer's ball (losing hazard).
The thorax of an insect. See Trunk, n., 5.
